This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks for segmentation indicates that it could be in cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The focus on robotic surgery suggests that it could also be in cs.RO (Robotics). The use of machine learning techniques for segmentation could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of residual learning and dilated convolutions suggests that it could be in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
